{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-15",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_15_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 15 - Officials",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 248.352,
  "page_end_sec": 492.16,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.734,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 248.352,
      "end": 248.92,
      "text": "That's out!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 249.12,
      "end": 251.1,
      "text": "You know it as well as I do."
    },
    {
      "start": 252.06,
      "end": 253.48,
      "text": "You'd think you wasn't a dick yourself,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 253.8,
      "end": 254.06,
      "text": "the way"
    },
    {
      "start": 254.12,
      "end": 255.34,
      "text": "you bellyache over things."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.78,
      "end": 259.94,
      "text": "I suppose you don't never pull the same stuff on anybody that",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 259.94,
      "end": 261.12,
      "text": "we pulled on you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 262.08,
      "end": 263.82,
      "text": "\"'You mean that you tried to pull on me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 263.9,
      "end": 264.14,
      "text": "Tom."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.36,
      "end": 265.31,
      "text": "Just tried.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.656,
      "end": 268.4,
      "text": "Polehouse swore under his breath and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 268.4,
      "end": 270.18,
      "text": "attacked the remainder of his pig's foot."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.2,
      "end": 271.64,
      "text": "Spade said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 272.76,
      "end": 273.16,
      "text": "All right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 273.34,
      "end": 274.52,
      "text": "You know it's out,"
    },
    {
      "start": 274.64,
      "end": 275.82,
      "text": "and I know it's out."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.44,
      "end": 277.34,
      "text": "What does Dundee know?"
    },
    {
      "start": 278.5,
      "end": 279.46,
      "text": "He knows it's out.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 280.54,
      "end": 281.3,
      "text": "What woke him up?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 282.22,
      "end": 282.66,
      "text": "Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 282.78,
      "end": 283.12,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 283.42,
      "end": 285.02,
      "text": "he never really thought you'd—"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.76,
      "end": 288.26,
      "text": "The irony in Spade's smile checked Polehouse.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 289.28,
      "end": 291.12,
      "text": "He'd left the sentence incomplete and said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 291.89,
      "end": 293.7,
      "text": "We dug up Thursby's record.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 294.1,
      "end": 294.9,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 294.98,
      "end": 295.88,
      "text": "who was he?"
    },
    {
      "start": 297.248,
      "end": 300.46,
      "text": "Polehouse's shrewd small brown eyes studied Spade's face.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 301.504,
      "end": 303.04,
      "text": "Spade exclaimed irritably,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 303.75,
      "end": 306.08,
      "text": "\"'I wish to God I knew half as much about"
    },
    {
      "start": 306.08,
      "end": 308.62,
      "text": "this business as you smart guys think I do.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.74,
      "end": 312.24,
      "text": "\"'I wish we all did,' Polehouse grumbled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 313.52,
      "end": 314.02,
      "text": "\"'Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 314.28,
      "end": 315.1,
      "text": "he was a St."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.18,
      "end": 317.06,
      "text": "Louis gunman the first we hear of him."
    },
    {
      "start": 317.45,
      "end": 319.16,
      "text": "He was picked up a lot back"
    },
    {
      "start": 319.34,
      "end": 320.42,
      "text": "there for this and that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.54,
      "end": 322.36,
      "text": "but he belonged to the Egan mob,"
    },
    {
      "start": 322.54,
      "end": 323.88,
      "text": "so nothing much was ever done"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.08,
      "end": 324.88,
      "text": "about any of it."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.37,
      "end": 327.88,
      "text": "I don't know how come he left that shelter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.12,
      "end": 329.62,
      "text": "but they got him once in"
    },
    {
      "start": 329.62,
      "end": 331.82,
      "text": "New York for knocking over Rove's dust games."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.56,
      "end": 333.7,
      "text": "His twist turned him up,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 333.78,
      "end": 334.98,
      "text": "and was in a year"
    },
    {
      "start": 335.08,
      "end": 336.32,
      "text": "before Fallon sprung him."
    },
    {
      "start": 337.14,
      "end": 339.64,
      "text": "A couple of years later he did a short hitch",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 339.64,
      "end": 341.84,
      "text": "in Joliet for pistol-whipping another twist"
    },
    {
      "start": 341.84,
      "end": 343.16,
      "text": "that had given him the needle,"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.34,
      "end": 347.16,
      "text": "but after that he took up with Dixie Monaghan and didn't"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.16,
      "end": 349.88,
      "text": "have much trouble getting out whenever he happened to get in."
    },
    {
      "start": 351.04,
      "end": 351.86,
      "text": "That's when Dixie was",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 351.94,
      "end": 354.75,
      "text": "almost as big a shot as Nick the Greek in Chicago gambling."
    },
    {
      "start": 356.1,
      "end": 357.92,
      "text": "This Thursby was Dixie's bodyguard,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 358.12,
      "end": 359.68,
      "text": "and he took the run out with him"
    },
    {
      "start": 359.68,
      "end": 363.22,
      "text": "when Dixie got in wrong with the rest of the boys over some debts he"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.4,
      "end": 364.68,
      "text": "couldn't or wouldn't pay off."
    },
    {
      "start": 365.76,
      "end": 367.02,
      "text": "That was a couple of years back,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 367.26,
      "end": 367.71,
      "text": "about"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.12,
      "end": 370.54,
      "text": "the time the Newport Beach Boating Club was shut up."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.09,
      "end": 372.12,
      "text": "I don't know if"
    },
    {
      "start": 372.18,
      "end": 373.64,
      "text": "Dixie had anything to do with that."
    },
    {
      "start": 373.96,
      "end": 374.56,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 374.8,
      "end": 376.42,
      "text": "this is the first time him"
    },
    {
      "start": 376.58,
      "end": 378.5,
      "text": "or Thursby's been seen since.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 379.648,
      "end": 381.62,
      "text": "\"'Dixie's been seen?' Spade asked.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 382.528,
      "end": 383.48,
      "text": "Polhaus shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 384.14,
      "end": 385.14,
      "text": "\"'No.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 386.04,
      "end": 387.64,
      "text": "His small eyes became sharp,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 387.82,
      "end": 388.38,
      "text": "prying."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.344,
      "end": 390.66,
      "text": "\"'Not unless you've seen him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 390.74,
      "end": 392.544,
      "text": "or know somebody's seen him.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 393.664,
      "end": 396.68,
      "text": "Spade lounged back in his chair and began to make a cigarette.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 398.112,
      "end": 400.04,
      "text": "\"'I haven't,' he said mildly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 400.8,
      "end": 402.496,
      "text": "\"'This is all new stuff to me.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 403.584,
      "end": 405.74,
      "text": "\"'I'll bet you,' Polhaus snorted.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 406.752,
      "end": 407.92,
      "text": "Spade grinned and asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 408.61,
      "end": 411.01,
      "text": "Where'd you pick up all the news about Thursby?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 412.16,
      "end": 413.36,
      "text": "\"'Some of it's on the records.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 414.22,
      "end": 415.24,
      "text": "The rest—well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 415.52,
      "end": 417.02,
      "text": "we got it here and there.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 418.208,
      "end": 418.88,
      "text": "\"'From Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 418.94,
      "end": 419.808,
      "text": "for instance?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 420.86,
      "end": 422.6,
      "text": "Now Spade's eyes held a sharp,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 422.64,
      "end": 423.6,
      "text": "prying gleam."
    },
    {
      "start": 424.896,
      "end": 427.28,
      "text": "Polehouse put down his coffee-cup and shook his head.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 428.064,
      "end": 428.96,
      "text": "\"'Not a word of it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 429.48,
      "end": 431.232,
      "text": "You poisoned that guy for us.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.968,
      "end": 432.66,
      "text": "Spade laughed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 433.4,
      "end": 436.18,
      "text": "You mean a couple of high-class sleuths like",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 436.18,
      "end": 438.22,
      "text": "you and Dundee worked on that lily of the"
    },
    {
      "start": 438.22,
      "end": 440.192,
      "text": "valley all night and couldn't crack him?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 441.38,
      "end": 441.88,
      "text": "\"'What do you mean,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 441.96,
      "end": 442.5,
      "text": "all night?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 443.296,
      "end": 444.36,
      "text": "Polehouse protested.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 444.8,
      "end": 447.08,
      "text": "\"'We worked on him for less than a couple of hours,"
    },
    {
      "start": 447.32,
      "end": 449.18,
      "text": "saw we wasn't getting any wares,"
    },
    {
      "start": 449.22,
      "end": 449.95,
      "text": "and let him go.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.328,
      "end": 453.42,
      "text": "Spade laughed again and looked at his watch.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 454.04,
      "end": 456.6,
      "text": "He caught John's eye and asked for their check."
    },
    {
      "start": 458.528,
      "end": 459.88,
      "text": "\"'I've got a date with the D.A.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 459.9,
      "end": 460.84,
      "text": "this afternoon,'"
    },
    {
      "start": 461.36,
      "end": 462.6,
      "text": "he told Polehouse while they"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.72,
      "end": 463.58,
      "text": "waited for his change."
    },
    {
      "start": 464.72,
      "end": 465.632,
      "text": "\"'He send for you?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.86,
      "end": 466.74,
      "text": "\"'Yes.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.648,
      "end": 469.6,
      "text": "Polehouse pushed his chair back and stood up,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 469.7,
      "end": 471.42,
      "text": "a barrel-bellied tall man,"
    },
    {
      "start": 471.64,
      "end": 472.34,
      "text": "solid and"
    },
    {
      "start": 472.44,
      "end": 472.88,
      "text": "phlegmatic."
    },
    {
      "start": 474.848,
      "end": 477.1,
      "text": "\"'You won't be doing me any favor,' he said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 477.66,
      "end": 479.328,
      "text": "by telling him I've talked to you.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 481.72,
      "end": 484.78,
      "text": "A levy youth with salient ears ushered",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 484.78,
      "end": 486.72,
      "text": "Spade into the district attorney's office."
    },
    {
      "start": 487.744,
      "end": 489.24,
      "text": "Spade went in smiling easily,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 489.5,
      "end": 490.52,
      "text": "saying easily,"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.8,
      "end": 491.46,
      "text": "Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 491.6,
      "end": 492.16,
      "text": "Brian.\""
    }
  ]
}